#### System information

Geth version: v1.5.5-stable-ff07d548/linux/go1.7.4
OS & Version: Kali GNU/Linux Rolling 64-bit
Commit hash : (if `develop`)

#### Expected behaviour
eth.compile.solidity(contract) should produce abi codes and other stuff

#### Actual behaviour
it appears to produce bytecodes, but abi is empty and any reference to compiled object says contract is undefined

#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour on the geth javascript console:
1) contract = 'contract mortal { /* Define variable owner of the type address*/ address owner; /* this function is executed at initialization and sets the owner of the contract */ function mortal() { owner = msg.sender; } /* Function to recover the funds on the contract */ function kill() { if (msg.sender == owner) suicide(owner); } } contract greeter is mortal { /* define variable greeting of the type string */ string greeting; /* this runs when the contract is executed */ function greeter(string _greeting) public { greeting = _greeting; } /* main function */ function greet() constant returns (string) { return greeting; } }';

2) contractCompiled = eth.compile.solidity(contract);
this results in the following on the console:


{
  /tmp/geth-compile-solidity101073083:greeter: {
    code: "",
    info: {
      abiDefinition: [{...}, {...}, {...}],
      compilerOptions: "--combined-json bin,abi,userdoc,devdoc --add-std --optimize",
      compilerVersion: "0.4.10",
      developerDoc: {
        methods: {}
      },
      language: "Solidity",
      languageVersion: "0.4.10",
      source: "contract mortal { /* Define variable owner of the type address*/ address owner; /* this function is executed at initialization and sets the owner of the contract */ function mortal() { owner = msg.sender; } /* Function to recover the funds on the contract */ function kill() { if (msg.sender == owner) suicide(owner); } } contract greeter is mortal { /* define variable greeting of the type string */ string greeting; /* this runs when the contract is executed */ function greeter(string _greeting) public { greeting = _greeting; } /* main function */ function greet() constant returns (string) { return greeting; } }",
      userDoc: {
        methods: {}
      }
    }
  },
  /tmp/geth-compile-solidity101073083:mortal: {
    code: "",
    info: {
      abiDefinition: [{...}, {...}],
      compilerOptions: "--combined-json bin,abi,userdoc,devdoc --add-std --optimize",
      compilerVersion: "0.4.10",
      developerDoc: {
        methods: {}
      },
      language: "Solidity",
      languageVersion: "0.4.10",
      source: "contract mortal { /* Define variable owner of the type address*/ address owner; /* this function is executed at initialization and sets the owner of the contract */ function mortal() { owner = msg.sender; } /* Function to recover the funds on the contract */ function kill() { if (msg.sender == owner) suicide(owner); } } contract greeter is mortal { /* define variable greeting of the type string */ string greeting; /* this runs when the contract is executed */ function greeter(string _greeting) public { greeting = _greeting; } /* main function */ function greet() constant returns (string) { return greeting; } }",
      userDoc: {
        methods: {}
      }
    }
  }
}

You can see the abi elements are empty. When I try to reference them,
> contractCompiled.greeter.info.abiDefinition
TypeError: Cannot access member 'info' of undefined

Either geth or eth invokes the compiler with the --combined-json option as shown - could that be the problem? How can any of that be changed? The solc team said they recommend using solcjs now instead of the solc binary, but that is said to be orders of magnitude slower, and introduces needless complexity imho.
